
How To Install a TestFarm Server ?

- install libapache2-mod-python ( version >= 3.1 )

- $ cd /etc/apache2/conf.d 

- $ sudo ln -s /your/path/to/testfarm/mod_python_testfarm.conf

- edit mod_python_testfarm.conf 
  change the Alias /testfarm_server to point to  /your/path/to/testfarm/server_side.py
  change DirectoryMatch to point to /you/path/to/testfarm

- check that the testfarm/server_side.py file is accessible by a different
  user. Tip check this: 
    $ sudo su nobody
    $ ls -l /you/paht/co/testfarm/server_side.py

- $ sudo /etc/init.d/apache2 restart

- give permissions to the logs and html directory. TODO explain


